.TH "snd_ctl_new" 9 "snd_ctl_new" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ctl_new \- create a new control instance with some elements
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ctl_new
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol **kctl "  ","
.BI "unsigned int count "  ","
.BI "unsigned int access "  ","
.BI "struct snd_ctl_file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kctl" 12
the pointer to store new control instance
.IP "count" 12
the number of elements in this control
.IP "access" 12
the default access flags for elements in this control
.IP "file" 12
given when locking these elements
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates a memory object for a new control instance. The instance has
elements as many as the given number (\fIcount\fP). Each element has given
access permissions (\fIaccess\fP). Each element is locked when \fIfile\fP is given.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, error code on failure
